<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0147-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Signed: a letter not in the authors handwriting, but signed by the author ]">LS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0146&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-04-02-0146-fn-0001#GEWN-02-04-02-0146-fn-0001" class="document">William Fairfax to GW, this date, n.1</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>On GWs orders George Mercer had borrowed 250 from William Cocks of Winchester for public use while GW was away at Fort Cumberland. See Kirkpatricks account at end of this letter. Also see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0112" class="document">GWs Memorandum, 8 June</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0116" class="document">GW to John Robinson, 10 June</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0190" class="document">10 July</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-04-02-0179" class="document">Robinson to GW, 29 June 1757</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Alexander Boyd had left Williamsburg by 20 June.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>Presumably Kirkpatrick, who had been GWs secretary in the Virginia
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-04-02-pb-0239">[239]</span>
Regiment, was referring to the reorganization of the regiment ordered by Dinwiddie on 16 May 1757.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0147-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>Kirkpatrick added this material below his signature.</p>

</div>
